2) Write a Python program to accept a list of integers and Count the number of 
even and odd elements and display all even elements in one list and odd 
elements in another list.

numbers = list(map(int, input("Enter numbers separated by space: ").split()))
even_list = []
odd_list = []
for num in numbers:
 if num % 2 == 0:
 even_list.append(num)
 else:
 odd_list.append(num)
print("Even numbers count:", len(even_list))
print("Odd numbers count:", len(odd_list))
print("Even numbers list:", even_list)
print("Odd numbers list:", odd_list)
